$ sysdm.cpl: Advanced -> Startup and Recovery

System startup:
  • Default operating system (drop down)
  • Time to display list of operating systems (yes/no)
  • Time to display recovery options when needed (yes/no)

System failure
  • Write an event to the system log (yes/no)
  • Automatically restart (yes/no)
  • Write debugging information (choose kind of dump)
  • Select dump file destination (default: `%SystemRoot%\MEMORY.DMP`)
  • Can dump files be overwritten (yes/no)
  • Disable automatic deletion of memory dumps when disk space is low.
